content: They keep coming from the direction of the border.
Just a constant wave after wave.
You know your training. Lock it down.
It's not smart to go to sleep unless it's safe.
How long till the next wave hits?
One hour from the north, two from the south.
Northern wave's thicker than fleas on a farm dog, but the southern's more dispersed.
By my estimation, we'll be fighting into the night again.
Yeah, can't push 'em too much further.
The north border. Now. - Call off your walkers. - Not us.
Go to the border, lay down your weapons, and wait.
Why's she want to talk with us?
Again. You have to answer for that.
We don't have to do anything.
We could just not go. - That's a bad idea. - We're already under attack.
If she wanted you dead, she'd send the horde.
All of it, not just a few waves at a time.
Maybe she's trying to wear us down first.
Or, as I relayed to you all at the beginning of this meeting, there's plausible reason to believe that the satellite and fire...
I don't want to hear about the damn satellite anymore, Eugene!
My friends died trying to save yours and ended up with their heads on spikes.
So all I want to hear from you is that you're gonna take a dozen of us to meet these freaks at the border and that we're gonna take that lead bitch's head off!
And then we'll put their heads on spikes!
Yeah. Yeah, I just need to get some air.
How many walkers did you see in Alpha's horde?
What's your plan for taking them out?
If she sends that horde, that's it!
Right now, all she wants to do is talk.
And we are going to listen.
Now, while we are doing that, everyone here needs to focus on what's coming in from the north and the south.
And it is going to get worse before it gets better.
But we aren't gonna get through it at all if we do not act as one.
Gabriel will take point in guarding the gate from the northern wave... while Aaron will take some troops and handle the southern wave, breaking it up before it hits the wall.
That leaves us, and the border. - Unarmed. - You're really going in there unarmed?
We got no choice. - We're good. - You're low on soldiers already.
The ones you have are fighting fatigue.
Negan has only been on cleanup duty.
Look, man, if it's all the same to you,
I'd rather just stay here and pick tomatoes and bury corpses.
Yeah, I need me in here, especially on a day like today.
I mean, look around... everybody's amped to 11, pissed at the skins, stirring shit up with each other.
I told you, I don't want any of those hateful vibes taken out on me.
Look, I just want to stay here.
Can you just do me that solid, Gabe?
You're taking him. End of discussion.
Good on you, puttin' the ol' stump to use.
I'm pretty sure that God put this here for a reason... to help me, help you... - Put it down. - Look, we both know that this broomstick ain't cutting it.
I am trying to make things better, and I am not that guy that you think...
Thanks for coming out with me.
I could... I could go all night.
You wanna go back, don't you?
There was one rule between our people.
That fire would've destroyed your land.
We have no conflict with nature.
It could've wiped out one of our communities.
We were not gonna sit back and let that happen.
During the fire, you walked my land.
And during the winter storm, you walked my land.
During your search along the river, you and the man with the metal arm walked my land.
What did I tell you about crossing my border?
There will be no bloodshed this time.
The creek that winds into the valley.
That is your new southern border.
We will mark the new border to the north.
That'll cut off our hunting grounds.
We don't have to stand here and listen to this...
Carol! "To this"... what? - To this bullshit. - That's it.
Not until this one lowers her eyes to my feet.
I look at you and I feel nothing at all.
The blonde boy... screamed your name just before we took his head.
And you know what she lost.
I know that you're dealing with...
She ain't been the same since she got off that boat.
Maybe she's better off on it.
She's out all night looking for them.
Whisperers. - Three of them. - Walkies on.
Split up... north, west. We'll take east.
What, do you want me to hang myself?
Tie up. I'm taking you back.
That is the best freaking news I've had all day!
But I am not tying up like some P.O.W.
What the hell is wrong with you?
I've been puttin' my neck on a block for you people all goddamn day!
You don't give a damn about us.
If you gave a shit, you'd leave.
I did what I had to do back then.
Tell me why the love of my life had to die.
One truth kept my people going... if you don't protect what belongs to you, then sooner or later, it belongs to someone else.
That goes for your land, your wallet, your home, your country... everything.
It is your job as a man to protect it.
That's the story of America, the story of the whole goddamn world.
And ain't nothing changing it... not you, not me, nobody.
Are you saying that Eric's death was my fault?
If I failed Eric... then you failed your wife. - Careful. - Yeah.
And you will never see her again.
All right. I'll meet you back at the creek.
Carol... how long you been taking those pills for?
Since I got back. It's fine.
They're like coffee. We can't stay out here.
Find a place with walls, hole up for a little while.
You two, get down here. - Gotcha. - Keep watch on the east end. - I'll take first watch. - All right.
He used to tell Merle and I all these crazy stories about his trips.
This one time, he was flying through Kentucky on I-66, and it's pitch-black outside.
He sees this girl up on the side of the road, looks like she's crying.
As he gets closer, the girl steps right out into the freeway, right in front of his truck.
He slams on the brakes, calls the local PD, gets out, and goes lookin' for her.
He looks under the cab, nothin'.
No dent in the grille, no blood, no nothin'.
See, my dad didn't sleep much, either.
Sometimes he'd stay up 24 hours just to make one of his runs.
You stay up that long, you start seeing things.
Daryl, I'm not a meth-snorting truck driver like...
Flowers growing outta the walkers is hogweed. - Hogweed? - Nasty shit.
Causes rashes, blindness. - Is it permanent? - Sometimes.
We'll leave first thing in the morning.
I mean, if that's okay with you.
This isn't your dad seeing a ghost. - What? - The story of the girl when your dad was a truck driver.
My dad wasn't a truck driver.
She fell. She cut her arm real bad.
Gonna need you all to leave.
Okay, you pull the shard, clamp open the wound, and I'll go in.
She's all patched up and out like a light.
You were mean as a mama wasp out there.
All of the above. - Rosita, where's Coco? - Probably sleeping.
I think you confused my query for "action" when I was trying to discern "locale."
She's with Barbara. - Is that okay? - It's just... that little nugget can't grow up without her mama.
I went out with you today to protect you - because I care about you. - Protect me?
I taught you how to fight.
You and I are never going to happen.
I need you to hear that.
I'm sorry that was harsh. I'm...
Are you familiar with the expression, "A drunk mind speaks a sober heart?"
When under the influence, inhibitions are lowered.
Sleep deprivation lowers inhibition, enhances impulsivity in a similar manner.
Thus, when you say, "It's not gonna happen," it's unfiltered truth straight from your ticker.
I've been trying to tell you that.
And I did not listen. 'Cause I thought that, perhaps someday, there might be something special between you and yours truly.
But there's nothing there. There never was.
You think that our friendship is just nothing?
I don't mean to eat sorrow by the spoonful in front of you, but I'm in the midst of experiencing a crushing moment of clarity.
Our... Our whole friendship is premised on my mistaken belief that, perhaps someday, I could change your mind, that... you would see that I was worthy enough of being re-zoned into love-town.
What kind of friend is that?
I should be asking you that.
Lack of sleep is my baseline reality.
You had that look in the meeting hall...
Okay. Come on, man. - I... Look, I gotta go to sleep. - Oh, no.
That's why I brought it over.
You know I saw combat in Iraq?
Yeah, I was a field medic.
And you are telling me this now?
Well, I don't like talking about it unless I have to, so...
You go in one person, come out different.
Like, this was the dude that never broke.
Came back with the shakes, the thousand-mile stare, the flashbacks, going in and out of VAs.
He was a mess... "He was"? "Was"? What...
You're having a drink with him.
There's probably some at the store. Hold on. - There you go. - Thank you.
You sure they're open right now?
And that's her fault. You shouldn't have stopped me.
There were seven of us out there.
I had to think of them.
